4447:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           whatever number of DMA data transfers (number of
4448:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC conversions).
4449:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           This ADC mode is intended to be used with DMA mode circular.
4450:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   If ADC DMA requests mode is set to unlimited and DMA is set to
4451:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         mode non-circular:
4452:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         when DMA transfers size will be reached, DMA will stop transfers of
4453:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC conversions data ADC will raise an overrun error
4454:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *        (overrun flag and interruption if enabled).
4455:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   For devices with several ADC instances: ADC multimode DMA
4456:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         settings are available using function @ref LL_ADC_SetMultiDMATransfer().
